        "timestamp": "2018-01-19 14:24:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> (2 comments)\n\nFor MainScreenHeader.jsx -> Why not? The code was cramped and more difficult to read. We should have new lines between our functions.\n\nFor NetworkCalls.js -> This file is full of generic network calls but for some reason the GET had very specific code that makes it incompatible with other use cases. These calls should be basic, and then specific response handling should be implemented in the action class that's making the call. That's the pattern we've followed everywhere. I see no valid reason to break it for a GET call.\n\n > (2 comments)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
